HEADWORD: Nibelungs
<hw>Ni"be*lungs</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>;
<sing><it>sing.</it> <singw>Nibelung</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr> </sing>.
<def>In German mythology, the children of the mist, a race of dwarfs or
demonic beings, the original possessors of the famous hoard and ring won
by Siegfried; also, the Burgundian kings in the Nibelungenlied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

